parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can increase the risk of accidents or injuries, as the driver may not be able to alert other road users or pedestrians in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn is inoperable
no warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncontrolled rolling of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or property damage, especially if the vehicle rolls into traffic or hits objects.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backwards down the driveway
even when shifted into park
and can continue to roll across streets and into other objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the display/navigation screen can cause distraction while driving, especially at night, and can also lead to safety issues if the backup camera is not functioning.
symptoms: The display/navigation screen does not always light up
sometimes taking a while to start working; when it doesn't work
the AC works autonomously
but cannot be turned off or adjusted
and the warning sensors
camera
and radio do not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and in some cases, engine fires can occur, posing a significant risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: Engine failure
engine blowing up
check engine codes P0720 and P0500
vehicle catching on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Erratic idle and excessive braking can lead to accidents, especially when stopping at traffic signals or in parking spaces, and can cause emotional distress to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: Engine idle increases when braking
excessive braking required to stop
vehicle wants to lurch forward
concern about being ready to stop quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the door to become stuck in the locked position, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door will not unlock or open
the door is stuck in the locked position
only one door is affected while others function normally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof glass can cause a loud noise, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from flying glass shards.
symptoms: Loud popping or shattering sound
sunroof glass breaks or shatters without any apparent cause
glass may not fall into the vehicle but remains on the roof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or accelerates suddenly without warning
often when applying the brakes or shifting gears
and may not respond to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning electronic throttle control can cause unintended acceleration, loss of power, or jerking movements, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine RPM revs up without warning
the vehicle surges or accelerates suddenly
the vehicle loses power or hesitates
the vehicle jerks forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly diagnose and repair issues can lead to continued safety risks, accidents, and injuries, as well as erosion of trust in dealerships and manufacturers.
symptoms: Dealerships or service centers fail to diagnose or repair issues
dismissing customer concerns or attributing problems to driver error
and may perform incomplete or ineffective repairs.
